The paper presents a deep neural network architecture for non-intrusive load monitoring, which involves estimating the power consumption of individual appliances from measurements of the total power consumption of a home. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep neural networks for energy disaggregation also involves techniques from neural networks (cs.NE) and signal processing (cs.SD). The paper also mentions the use of convolutional layers in the network architecture, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another possible sub-category.
